t.me/gena460_bot

Congratulations on my bot. You will find it in Telegram at @gena460_bot.

Commands, what used for the building:

1. Clone new repo:
$ git clone https://github.com/gena460/kbot.git

2. Initializing new Go project:
$ go mod init github.com/gena460/kbot

3. Install useful template for the new Golang project:
$ go install github.com/spf13/cobra-cli@latest

4. Initializing CLI:
$ cobra-cli init

5. Add Cobra - CLI library for Go that empowers applications. This application is a tool to generate the needed files
to quickly create a Cobra application.:
$ cobra-cli add version

6. Help module:
$ go run main.go help

7. Version module:
$ go run main.go version

8. Add necessary for binary file with name kbot:
$ cobra-cli add kbot

9. Add contexts in the files version.go, kbot.go

10. Build project
$ go build -ldflags "-X="github.com/gena460/kbot/cmd.appVersion=v1.0.0

11. Run binary
./kbot

12. Check version 
./kbot version

13. Create in repo's folder file .gitignore
touch .gitignore

14. Add binary file with name "kbot" to .gitignore

15. Add new context in the file kbot.go

16. Format Golang files:
gofmt -s -w ./

17. Add dependencies
go get

18. Build new version
go build -ldflags "-X="github.com/gena460/kbot/cmd.appVersion=v1.0.1

19. Run new version kbot:
./kbot
Usage:
  kbot [command]

Available Commands:
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  help        Help about any command
  kbot        A brief description of your command
  version     A brief description of your command

Flags:
  -h, --help     help for kbot
  -t, --toggle   Help message for toggle

Use "kbot [command] --help" for more information about a command.

20. Modified kbot.go

21. Rebuild version 1.0.1:
$ go build -ldflags "-X="github.com/gena460/kbot/cmd.appVersion=v1.0.1

22. Start with argument:
./kbot start
kbot v1.0.1 started2023/05/01 04:18:30 Please, check TELE_TOKEN env variable. telegram: Not Found (404)

23. Add own bot via official Telegram helpers @BotFather:
/newbot

24. Choose name and address for bot:
kbot
gena460_bot

25. Copy token from @BotFather to access the HTTP API

26. Paste Ctrl+V token after executing next command:
$ read -s TELE_TOKEN

27. Check token as Variable:
$ echo $TELE_TOKEN

28. Export Variable:
$ export TELE_TOKEN

29. Start program
$ ./kbot start

30. Make changes in kbot.go

31. Build new version 1.0.2
$ go build -ldflags "-X="github.com/gena460/kbot/cmd.appVersion=v1.0.2


32. Find and check bot from Telegram
@gena460_bot
/start
/start hello
